---
// Empathy/problem section - names the user's frustration
// StoryBrand principle: Name the problem to create emotional resonance
---

<section class="problem-strip">
  <p class="problem-text">
    You've got 47 tabs open. You can't remember which one had that crucial article. You're scared to close any of them. Sound familiar?
  </p>
</section>

<style>
  .problem-strip {
    background-color: var(--muted);
    padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .problem-text {
    color: var(--muted-foreground);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 48rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .problem-strip {
      padding: 3rem 2rem;
    }

    .problem-text {
      font-size: 1.125rem;
    }
  }
</style>
